Description: Fix display and input of UTF-8 accented characters in GUI file browser
 The GUI file selection dialog failed to display or accept filenames with
 accented characters (e.g. é, è, à).
 .
 Three bugs were fixed:
 .
 1. wg_fontengine: RenderGlyph() and GetMetrics() accepted a plain 'char',
    causing UTF-8 bytes >= 0x80 to be sign-extended into large invalid
    FT_ULong values when passed to FT_Load_Char().  Changed to FT_ULong.
 .
 2. wg_renderedstring: GetMetrics() and Draw() iterated the string byte
    by byte, rendering each byte as a separate glyph.  Multi-byte UTF-8
    sequences produced garbled output (e.g. "é" appeared as "Ã©").
    Now decodes UTF-8 on the fly; continuation bytes get zero-width rects
    so all byte-based cursor indices in wg_editbox remain valid.
 .
 3. wg_editbox TEXTINPUT handler: explicitly filtered every byte with the
    high bit set ("Ignore extended ASCII chars"), silently discarding all
    accented characters typed by the user.  For content type ANY the whole
    UTF-8 text is now inserted directly.  BACKSPACE and DELETE were also
    fixed to erase complete UTF-8 sequences instead of single bytes.
